{"behaviors":[{"behavior_id":1,"description":"The content passed to the summary-generation step includes data retrieved from all three sources.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"Failure boundary is cross-module handoff: three collectors -> aggregation/orchestration -> summary input. Unit is too low because the behavior is about wiring between modules, not one pure function. No required real OS/network/subprocess at assertion point (sources can be stubbed in-process), so System is rejected. No dependence on model output quality (only payload passed into summary step), so Agentic/Workflow are rejected.","test_description":"Wire the real data-collection orchestrator with three in-process source adapters (metrics, issue tracker, deployment log) returning distinct sentinel fields; execute one report build and assert the exact summary-input payload contains all three source sections and expected keys.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.25,"Integration":0.7,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":2,"description":"When one data source is unavailable, the report is produced with a `data unavailable` note for that section rather than aborting.","minimum_level":"Integration","justification":"This is error propagation across modules (source adapter failure -> report assembler fallback section text). Unit is too low because fallback behavior depends on module interaction/state handoff. System was considered, but rejected because behavior text only requires handling an unavailable source, which can be reproduced by an in-process adapter raising timeout/connection errors. No real AI-output dependence, so Agentic/Workflow are disqualified.","test_description":"Run report assembly with two normal in-process adapters and one adapter that raises an availability exception; assert run completes, report contains a `data unavailable` marker for only the failing section, and no global abort is raised.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.15,"Integration":0.65,"System":0.2,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0}},{"behavior_id":3,"description":"The narrative summary accurately represents the key values present in the input data.","minimum_level":"Agentic","justification":"Behavior targets output quality/faithfulness of generated narrative, which depends on real model judgment. Deterministic stubs would always pass and hide factual-drift or omission failures. Integration was considered but rejected because the behavior text is about summary accuracy, not routing/retries/payload shape around the model call. Workflow is rejected since only one agentic decision (summary generation) is required.","test_description":"Execute summary generation against the real model using a fixed dataset with critical numeric/key facts; score whether generated text preserves required facts (values/entities/trends) over repeated runs with acceptance thresholds for factual inclusion and contradiction rate.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.03,"Agentic":0.75,"Workflow":0.05}},{"behavior_id":4,"description":"A complete report — from data collection through email delivery — reaches the configured recipient's inbox correctly.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Failure boundary includes real external delivery and inbox receipt (real HTTP/API + real email transport/inbox behavior), which mocks can hide. Integration is too low because it cannot validate actual transport/inbox semantics. Agentic was considered and rejected because behavior text focuses on end-to-end delivery to inbox, not correctness of model-generated content; model output can be fixture-controlled without invalidating this delivery boundary. Workflow rejected: no multi-agentic chain requirement in behavior wording.","test_description":"Run the script end-to-end in a production-like environment against reachable source endpoints and a real mail service/test inbox; assert one scheduled execution produces an email received by configured recipient with expected report artifact attached/body present.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.02,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.7,"Agentic":0.1,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When the email delivery service is unreachable, the generated report is saved to a local file and delivery is retried on the next scheduled run.","minimum_level":"System","justification":"Behavior crosses process/runtime boundaries: outage handling plus durable file fallback plus next scheduled execution retry. Real filesystem persistence and separate-run behavior are core to failure mode; pure in-process mocks risk missing path/permission/process-state defects. Integration was considered, but rejected because behavior text explicitly requires retry on the next scheduled run (run-to-run persistence boundary). Agentic/Workflow are disqualified: no model-output quality or multi-agentic decision chain requirement.","test_description":"Execute run #1 with email endpoint unreachable and verify fallback report file is actually written on disk; execute run #2 in a fresh process with email reachable and verify queued fallback report is retried/sent and local fallback state is cleared/updated appropriately.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.03,"Integration":0.28,"System":0.62,"Agentic":0.03,"Workflow":0.04}}]}
